  "text": "Patient 61 demonstrated serious progressive metastatic disease that was treated with empiric 131 I and then external beam radiation therapy. He died of causes unrelated to his cancer [CITATION_1] . Conversely, patient 90 enrolled in this cohort with a Tg-on of 0.5 ng/ml or less and an rhTSH-Tg of 6.2 ng/ml. She subsequently demonstrated progressive metastatic disease to lungs and eventually bone, brain, and adrenal glands that culminated in her death 33.2 yr after her first thyroid cancer surgery and 9.0 yr after her enrollment rhTSH stratification despite tyrosine kinase inhibitor therapy for progressive systemic disease (10) and ␥-knife therapy for brain metastases.",
